<h2>Changing the default password</h2>
<p>
You may wish to change your password. This can be done by running the following command:
<pre>passwd</pre>
</p>
<h2>Enabling the root username</h2>
<p>
By default, OSMC ships with the root user disabled. You can enable it by typing the following command:
<pre>sudo passwd root</pre>
</p>
